The course will cover in-depth bio-waste management technologies and the possibilities of using bio-waste for energy purposes. The safe management of bio-waste is one of the key areas of the principles of sustainable development, ensuring the implementation of sustainable waste management technologies.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to learn about bio-waste management and bio-resource processing technologies, both in terms of their use for energy production and their valorisation in the production of materials.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student - has an overview of bio-resources at Estonian, European Union and global level; - acquires knowledge of the basics of bio-waste classification and environmentally sound methods of waste management.  - acquires knowledge of bio-waste management technologies and their characteristics. - analyses the potential use of bio-waste and the efficiency of technological methods; - knows the main options for energy recovery from bio-waste.
